<!-- 
	This file defines the ruleset for display types of metadata in metadata editor. 
	It is used by org.goobi.api.display.helper.DisplayRules and defines whether a given metadatum is displayed as dopdown list with one or
	more selections, input field or textarea.
	The file should be stored in your goobi configuration folder.
	You can define your own rules by manipulating this file. The Syntax is: 

	<ruleSet>
		<context projectName="your Project">
		defines for which project the definition will be used

			<bind>create or edit</bind>
		bindstate create is used if you create a new metadatum, edit is used, when metadatum allready exists

			<select tns:ref="some metadatum">
				<item tns:selected="true or false">
					<label>some label</label>
					<value>some value</value>
				</item>
				<item tns:selected="true or false">
						....
		The tag select defines a list of items for a selection list with more than one selections. Each item is presented with a label, that will be 
		presented in the UI and a value that will be stored in metadatum. With attribute tns:selected you can define, whether an item is preselected 
		or not.
			<select1 tns:ref="some metadatum">
				<item tns:selected="true or false">
					<label>some label</label>
					<value>some value</value>
				</item>
				<item tns:selected="true or false">
					.....
		The	select1 tag defines a list of items for a selection list with only one possible selection. 

			<input tns:ref="some metadatum">
				<label>some label</label>
			</input>
		The input tag defines that this metadatum is displayed as input field with the defined label.

			<textarea tns:ref="some metadatum">
				<label>some label</label>
			</textarea>
		The textarea tag defines that the metadatum is displayed as textarea with defined label.
		</context>	
	</ruleSet>

	For each project you have to define the display rules for metadata again.
-->

	
